hopobject.body: I'm unemployed fungsi obat micardis telmisartan 80 mg Breaking Bad creator Vince Gilligan has said "we're not going out with a whimper". But does Walter White (aka invincible drug-lord Heisenberg) die? And, if so, who kills him? Not his own returning cancer, although that would be poetic. Not even old partner Jesse, whom Walter murders. I bet on Walter to be taken down by cop brother-in-law Hank, with Walt's poor sap son Walt junior having to watch his father die. Walt's corrupt and cynical wife Skyler tries for witness protection in a deal brokered by shark lawyer Saul Goodman.
